```javascript
for (let i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
  const asciiCode = String.fromCharCode(i);
  const hexadecimalCode = i.toString(16).toUpperCase();

  console.log(`ASCII: ${asciiCode} (${i}) | Hex: ${hexadecimalCode}`);
}
```
This JavaScript program will generate and print out the ASCII character, decimal code, and hexadecimal code for characters from 0 to 7F. The `for` loop iterates through each integer value from 0 to 127, converting them into their respective ASCII characters using `String.fromCharCode()`. Then, it converts the integers into hexadecimal format using `toString(16).toUpperCase()`. Finally, it prints out the results using `console.log()`.
